text.tspan: Creates a memento containing a snapshot of its current internal state.
Stores internal state of the Originator object. The momento may store as much
or as little of the originator's internal state as necessary at its originator's discretion.
Is responsible for the momento's safekeeping.
Uses the memento to restore its internal state.
Never operates on or examines the contents of a memento.
Protects against access by objects other than the originator. Mementos have
effectively two interfaces. Caretaker sees a narow interface to the Momento - it can
only pass the memento to other objects. Originator, in contrast, sees a wide
interface, one that lets it access all the data necessary to restore itself to its
previous state. Ideally, only the originator that produced the momento would be
permitted to access the memento's internal state.
Without violating encapsulation, capture and externalize an object's internal state
so that the object can be restored to this state later.
